<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-04T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-04T20:00:00-05:00" n="190" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d190">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.5045/4: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the High Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-04T20:00:00-05:00">December 4, 1929—8
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>60. Your 90 December 4 noon. The Department does not desire you to take
                            such measures as you describe unless absolutely necessary for the
                            protection of lives. The situation as you have described it does not
                            seem to make such measures necessary.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>